subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat and distribution.

Nothria edwardsi


comb. nov.

is known from abyssal depths (
4020 to 4255 m
) of the central and eastern North Atlantic, including the Azores archipelago and the area comprised between Azores and the Iberian Peninsula (
Roule 1898
; 
1906
; 
Fauvel 1914
).
